Lattice as Lens

A lattice is essentially a filter for interactions.

For example:

Carbon Structure	What It Filters
Diamond	light passes, electrons blocked
Graphene	electrons flow easily
Graphite	layers slide easily

Same atoms.

Different information pathways.

⸻

Language Lattices Work the Same Way

Words arranged in different structures filter meaning and interpretation.

Example:

Analytical lattice

problem → cause → mechanism → solution

This lens emphasizes logic and causality.

⸻

Narrative lattice

hero → challenge → struggle → transformation

This lens emphasizes story and emotion.

⸻

Poetic lattice

image → metaphor → resonance → ambiguity

This lens emphasizes association and feeling.

⸻

The Lens Effect

Each structure lets certain ideas pass easily and blocks others.

Like this:

IDEA
 ↓
[LENS STRUCTURE]
 ↓
INTERPRETATION

Different lattice → different interpretation.

